---
description: Best practices for SQLAlchemy ORM usage
globs: **/*.{py}
---
- Use declarative base for defining models to simplify schema management.
- Implement proper transaction management with `session.begin()`.
- Use eager loading with `joinedload` or `subqueryload` to reduce N+1 queries.
- Leverage bulk operations for improved performance on large datasets.
- Use `indexes` and `constraints` to optimize database queries and ensure data integrity.